# Project defaults

- **Scope**: Change only what the task requires. No unrelated refactors or extra files.
- **Style**: Read neighboring code first; match naming, types, imports, and comment density.
- **Verification**: When the repo has scripts or tests, run the relevant ones after substantive edits. Use the terminal for a real environment when investigating failures.
- **Rules & skills**: Follow `.cursor/rules/` and any project skills when present.
- **Citations**: When pointing at code, use the workspace line-range format the editor expects so navigation is one click.

If requirements conflict, prefer the user’s explicit instructions for the current task.
